Reference-contexts: It is intuitively obvious that the optimal modelling order is dependent on the class of speech under consideration, and should, for the best performance, be estimated from the observed data alongside the other parameters. Here a model selection scheme based on the reversible jump MCMC sampler <ref> (Green, 1995) </ref> is adopted, since it can be seamlessly integrated into the overall MCMC estimation framework. The speech production model and estimation strategy presented here can potentially be applied to a wide range of speech processing problems. <p> Since points in C may vary in dimensionality, sampling from (40) cannot be performed by a standard Gibbs sampling step. Instead, a variable dimension scheme based on the reversible jump MCMC method <ref> (Green, 1995) </ref> is employed here. This scheme works by considering (p; a p ) as the current state in a Markov chain that has (40) as its invariant distribution.
